### VS Code REST Client / JetBrains HTTP file — click "Send Request" to try the API.
### Start the stack first: docker compose up --build

# ---- happy path -------------------------------------------------------------

### Create a user (201 Created + Location header)
POST http://localhost:3000/v1/users
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "alice",
  "password": "correct horse battery staple"
}

### Authenticate (200 OK)
POST http://localhost:3000/v1/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "alice",
  "password": "correct horse battery staple"
}

# ---- error surface (all RFC 9457 application/problem+json) ------------------

### Duplicate username → 409 USERNAME_TAKEN (case-insensitive!)
POST http://localhost:3000/v1/users
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "ALICE",
  "password": "another perfectly fine passphrase"
}

### Weak password → 422 WEAK_PASSWORD with every violated rule
POST http://localhost:3000/v1/users
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "bob",
  "password": "password"
}

### Wrong password → 401 INVALID_CREDENTIALS + RateLimit headers
POST http://localhost:3000/v1/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "alice",
  "password": "wrong password entirely here"
}

### Unknown user → the SAME 401, same timing (try to tell them apart!)
POST http://localhost:3000/v1/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "who-is-this",
  "password": "wrong password entirely here"
}

### Unknown field → 400 (rejected, never silently stripped)
POST http://localhost:3000/v1/users
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "carol",
  "password": "a perfectly acceptable passphrase",
  "admin": true
}

# ---- operations --------------------------------------------------------------

### Liveness
GET http://localhost:3000/healthz

### Readiness (checks Redis)
GET http://localhost:3000/readyz

### OpenAPI document
GET http://localhost:3000/docs/json
